Senior Product Controller
Robert Half United Kingdom
-
London
The Role
Oversee the daily and periodic reporting and the production of management information;
Take responsibility for ensuring that the P&L; is approved by the respective desk each day;
Provide MIS regulatory reporting as and when required and ensure the accuracy of the MIS;
Supervise the daily stop loss limit monitoring process;
Supervise the P&L; reconciliation process and the Balance Sheet and Off Balance Sheet reconciliation process;
Support the front office and ensure all queries are dealt with in an efficient manner;
Ensure that the necessary processes and procedures are in place to mitigate Operational Risks identified;
Liaise with Group Finance to manage all accounting queries including changes to accounting and tax regulations;
Help to develop and train staff;
Assist with strategic initiatives, including Global expansion and process automation.
Your Profile
Qualified Accountant - ACA/ACCA/CIMA;
5-10 years' experience of Product Control in a Treasury banking environment;
Strong knowledge of Treasury products including FX, fixed income/interest rate derivatives markets and structured products;
Solid understanding of IFRS and IAS as well as UK accounting and tax regulations;
Good communication skills and a hands on approach.
The Company
A global bank in Canary Wharf which is headquartered in Abu Dhabi. Reporting to the Head of Finance in London and the Head of Product Control in Abu Dhabi, the Senior Product Controller will play a key role in the day-to-day support of the London trading floor.
Salary & Benefits
The Senior Product Controller will be offered up to ÂŁ85,000 per annum, dependent on experience. Based in Canary Wharf after 1-2 months in Abu Dhabi. Robert Half Ltd acts as an employment business for temporary positions and an employment agency for permanent positions. Robert Half is committed to equal opportunity and diversity. Suitable candidates with equivalent qualifications and more or less experience can apply.
